                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Sidur for the entire year, Western Ashkenazi rite</summary>
                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Marshall_Or_133_3_a">
                            <locus>ff. 279r-373v</locus>
                            <title>Sidur for the entire year according to the Western Ashkenazi rite</title>
                            <title xml:lang="he">   סדור מנהג אשכנז המערבי לכל השנה</title>
                            <note>Third volume of a three-volume set; first volume: <ref target="/p/m/yje14x7qz12mh89d83q4ae4120">MS. Marshall Or. 133(1)</ref>; second volume <ref target="/p/m/78r8h08z4n3337cms4ntz2wayr">MS. Marshall Or. 133(2)</ref>.</note>
                            <note>Content: two sets of yotserot for circumcision (one by Eleazar ben Natan, the other by Avraham Kohen)  yotserot for Shabat shuvah, for Ḥol ha-moʿed Sukot, Shabat Parashat Ṿayirah, and Shabat Hanukah.            
                            </note>
                            <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                        </msItem>
